cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE. 

This paper is about Natural Language Question Answering, which is a subfield of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a modified version of the MAC net architecture, which is a deep learning model for attention-based reasoning. This makes it relevant to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses image data for some of the experiments, which brings in Computer Vision (cs.CV) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the iterative reasoning approach of MAC net is related to Neural Networks (cs.NE).
